WEBVTT

00:08.386 --> 00:14.194
Matthew chapter 20, Jesus is moving closer to Jerusalem, closer to his cross.

00:15.857 --> 00:23.848
And as he heads towards the cross, he teaches his disciples the values of God's kingdom and how God manifests God's authority and lordship.

00:25.771 --> 00:29.697
We're listening to Baudido Bay Methodist Church's podcast on the Gospel of Matthew.

00:30.337 --> 00:32.601
Today is Wednesday, February 25.

00:32.961 --> 00:36.306
And today we're reading Matthew chapter 20.

00:36.834 --> 00:40.899
Chapter 20 picks up where chapter 19 of Matthew ends.

00:41.900 --> 00:48.947
When Jesus said to his disciples, but many who are first will be last and the last shall be first.

00:50.249 --> 00:53.032
God overturns the values and assumptions of this world.

00:54.393 --> 00:57.136
For example, the world says, you should only get what you earn.

00:57.557 --> 00:59.259
You should receive what you deserve.

00:59.960 --> 01:01.481
Blessed are those who are first.

01:02.943 --> 01:05.746
And in today's reading, Jesus tells a parable

01:06.530 --> 01:11.557
of a vineyard owner who goes out early in the morning and hires laborers to work as vineyard.

01:13.340 --> 01:19.629
He and the laborers agree to a fair and just wage for the day's work, one denarius.

01:21.632 --> 01:36.274
The owner then goes back to where those who want to be laborers for the day hang out and are waiting for work and the owner sees people waiting and he hires more, he goes back at nine o'clock at noon at three o'clock and then at five p.m.

01:36.386 --> 01:41.111
And he keeps hiring people who are waiting for work.

01:41.131 --> 01:46.236
Then at sundown, he pays the laborers, starting with those who were hired last.

01:46.516 --> 01:51.381
And he gives those who just worked one hour.

01:51.401 --> 02:00.650
He gives them the same wage that he gives to those who were hired, the first thing in the morning.

02:01.271 --> 02:04.754
That is, he pays each of the workers, one denarius.

02:04.898 --> 02:33.074
the ones hired last just as much as he the ones hired first and as you can expect the first ones complain but the vineyard owner he did not cheat them he says to the first ones friends I'm doing you know wrong did you not agree with me for a denarius take what belongs to you and go I choose to give to the last the same as I give to you

02:33.794 --> 02:36.977
Am I not allowed to do what I choose with what belongs to me?

02:36.997 --> 02:40.641
Or are you envious because I am generous?

02:43.484 --> 02:48.789
Remember, the owner paid the laborers who were hired first exactly what they agreed upon.

02:49.350 --> 02:50.811
He did not cheat them at Daenerys.

02:50.831 --> 02:53.454
That's what it was the average wage, the typical wage.

02:53.494 --> 02:54.976
He gave them what they asked for.

02:54.996 --> 03:01.362
A sermon by Barbara Brown Taylor has helped me understand this parable.

03:01.986 --> 03:05.752
She says that a lot depends on where you see yourself in this parable.

03:07.094 --> 03:15.328
If we view ourselves as those who got hired first in the morning, then we will become envious and begrudge the owner for being generous.

03:16.650 --> 03:19.415
But what if we're not the ones who were hired first?

03:20.997 --> 03:23.181
But we were instead the ones hired last.

03:24.243 --> 03:28.690
See, then we will be overwhelmingly grateful

03:29.026 --> 03:31.931
and view the owner as being gracious and kind.

03:34.135 --> 03:36.719
This parable represents how God relates to us.

03:37.741 --> 03:48.039
And Barbara Brown Teller asks the question, what if from God's perspective, we are not the ones who showed up first, but we're those who came last to the vineyard.

03:48.059 --> 03:54.450
I think of people who have become followers of Christ while they're in prison.

03:54.914 --> 03:55.995
They know they've messed up.

03:56.015 --> 03:59.039
They know they sinned earlier and life and did some awful things.

03:59.859 --> 04:02.422
And then they come to faith in Christ later in life.

04:03.123 --> 04:06.467
And through this parable, Jesus assures them.

04:06.987 --> 04:12.554
He assures us that they too are God's beloved children and now members of the body of Christ.

04:13.875 --> 04:20.242
And maybe from God's perspective, we all are those who came late to work in the vineyard.

04:20.802 --> 04:25.787
And we all are recipients of God's amazing generosity and grace.

04:27.168 --> 04:29.771
So the last will be first and the first will be last.

04:32.914 --> 04:42.363
Another story in Matthew 20 is the story of James and John's mother asking Jesus for her sons to have positions of prominence when Jesus enters his kingdom.

04:42.624 --> 04:45.827
One sitting at his right, one sitting at his left.

04:46.467 --> 04:49.010
And Jesus responds, he responds by saying,

04:49.090 --> 04:51.573
You don't have a clue what you're asking.

04:51.633 --> 04:55.617
Are you able to drink the cup that I'm about to drink?

04:55.637 --> 04:57.299
See, Jesus is going to the cross.

04:57.339 --> 05:02.124
He's about to suffer and die to redeem humanity.

05:03.906 --> 05:06.989
And remember, Jesus is King.

05:07.049 --> 05:15.538
He's King of King and Lord of Lords, but he's not a Lord, a ruler, a King who lords it over others, who bullies others.

05:15.682 --> 05:19.746
He is a suffering servant who came to give his life for others.

05:20.727 --> 05:29.896
And when Jesus enters into his glory on the cross, the ones on his left and on his right are two criminals who are crucified with him.

05:31.237 --> 05:34.400
True greatness does not come from lording it over others.

05:34.621 --> 05:37.664
True greatness comes from having a servant heart.

05:38.985 --> 05:44.050
After talking with James and John and their mother and after hearing the other disciples grumble

05:44.290 --> 05:46.112
about what James and John asked.

05:47.293 --> 06:13.458
Jesus calls his disciples together and he says to them, he says, you know that the rulers of the Gentiles lord it over them and their great men exercise authority over them it shall not be so among you but whoever would be great among you must be your servant and whoever would be first among you must be your slave even as the son of man came not to be served but to serve

06:13.954 --> 06:16.241
and to give his life as a ransom for many.

06:18.728 --> 06:19.590
Thank you for listening.

06:20.613 --> 06:24.946
My name is Scott Home and this podcast is produced by Kenny Stewart.

